2 apple
2 pear
1 sachet Sweet Golden Spice Blend
20 g brown sugar
1 tbs water
100 g butter
1 packet Classic Oat Mix
1 packet vanilla custard

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut the apple and pear into
small chunks.
TIP: For a more traditional crumble, peel the fruit before cutting into chunk

In a medium baking dish, combine the apple, pear, sweet golden spice blend,
brown sugar, the water and a pinch of salt. Set aside. In a small saucepan,
melt the butter over a low heat. Add the classic oat mix and stir to combine.

Sprinkle the crumble mixture evenly over the spiced fruit. Bake until the
topping is golden and the fruit is tender, 20-25 minutes.
TIP: The fruit is cooked when you can pierce it easily with a fork.

Divide the spiced apple and pear crumble between bowls. Serve with the
vanilla custard.